 their luck, and of a crisis that is testing American democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aFinancial crisesxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aForeclosurexSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aForeclosurezUnited States. 0aMortgage loanszUnited States. 4aForeclosure crisis. 4acrime. 4ahousing. 4ainequality. 4amortgage lending. 4aneighborhoods. 4apolitical participation. 4apublic opinion. 4aunemployment. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh1 aNiedt, Christopher, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479578440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804795784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804795784.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles